{{Infobox institute |name = Transitional Justice Institute |image = |image_size = 250px |image_alt = Logo |caption = The institute's logo which encompasses the [[:File:Ulster University Logo.png|University logo<sup>(left)</sup>]] and the Institute's logo<sup>(right)</sup>. |latin_name = |motto = |founder = |established = 2003<ref name="About TJI ">{{cite web | url=http://www.transitionaljustice.ulster.ac.uk/tji_about.html | title=Transitional Justice Institute - About TJI | publisher=Ulster University | accessdate=December 22, 2014}}</ref> |mission = |focus = [[Transitional Justice]], [[Conflict (process)|Conflict]], [[Human Rights Law]], and [[International Law]] |president = |chairman = |head_label = |head = |faculty = |adjunct_faculty = |staff = |key_people = |budget = |subsidiaries = |owner = |non-profit_slogan = |location = |city = |state = |province = |country = |coor = |address = |website = [http://www.ulster.ac.uk/transitionaljustice www.ulster.ac.uk/transitionaljustice] |dissolved = |footnotes = }}
The Belfast Guidelines is a project led by Professor Louise Mallinder and Prof Tom Hadden of the [[Transitional Justice Institute]]. The Guidelines examine the principles concerning the legality and legitimacy of amnesties in states transitioning from conflict or authoritarian regimes.<ref>http://www.transitionaljustice.ulster.ac.uk/TransitionalJusticeInstitute.htmAmnestyGuidelinesProject.htm</ref> They were drafted by an expert group that included Prof [[David Kretzmer]] and Prof [[William Schabas]]. They have been widely translated into Arabic, Chinese, Malay, Portuguese, Russian, Spanish and Thai.
